# Nunchi outbound reply gate — per-direction override (EXAMPLE)
#
# Copy to ~/.claude/nunchi-pretool-reply.env. This file is sourced AFTER the
# shared ~/.claude/nunchi-gate.env by the outbound reply wrapper only, so its
# exports override the shared defaults for the outbound direction. Like the
# shared file, the installer never writes it — it is yours to keep and tune.
#
# Canonical use: narrow the peer roster on the OUTBOUND path.
#
# Why this differs from inbound: on the outbound path the gate tags each author
# in the recent context as "peer_bot" or "human" and feeds that to the
# classifier. Tagging a bot as "human" biases the gate toward SPEAK when that
# author is present; tagging it as "peer_bot" biases toward restraint. Keeping a
# bot OUT of the outbound roster (so it reads as "human" to your reply gate)
# counters over-suppression on turns genuinely addressed to you, while the
# inbound gate keeps the full roster so peer chatter still reads as peer chatter.
#
# This is the sturdy, visible place to tune outbound restraint — prefer editing
# this file over touching the gate internals.
export NUNCHI_HOOK_PEER_BOTS="PeerA"
